<exp_P@PopUp>:
    Label:
        text: "Buttons functionality and physical sense (from top to bottom and left to right): \n -Hamiltonian perturbative term: Anisotropy Energy (B) or Magnetic Field at x axis (hx), respectively. \n (Test what happens with spin tunneling interaction for each term.) \n -Spin Molecule: from 1 to 6 you can test how the system would behave. \n -Initial and final time: test the interval needed. \n (Try to be coherent aprox same time below 0 than over 0.) \n -D: Anisotropy energy that breaks the zero-field Zeeman degeneracacy. \n -h: magnetic field rythm of variation over time at z axis. \n -B or hx depending the Hamiltonian perturbative term. \n \n Then you can use SEND to compute the results with the information given. \n There are some demonstration examples for each spin and the \n video reproduction buttons to show how the system evolves."
        
        size_hint: 0.6, 0.8
        pos_hint: {"x":0.2, "top":1}
    	multiline: True
    			
    	halign:"left"


